snippet: Militants from Syria who overran a Lebanese town mostly withdrew across the rugged hills separating the two countries as a cease-fire appeared to hold Thursday.
abstract: Militants from Syria who overran a Lebanese town mostly withdraw across the rugged hills separating the two countries as a cease-fire appears to hold; Lebanese troops free seven soldiers and ambulances to evacuate dozens of casualties.
lead_paragraph: Militants from Syria who overran a Lebanese town mostly withdrew across the rugged hills separating the two countries as a cease-fire appeared to hold Thursday.

headline.main: Lebanon: Militants Begin to Leave Town
